<subSubSection id="C34A65180379EF661E897824FE8A6C95" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="75" pageId="6" pageNumber="74" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BEF36930379EF671E897824FEF76A30" blockId="6.[189,310,1879,1905]" box="[189,310,1879,1905]" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">
<heading id="D0A781FF0379EF671E897824FEF76A30" bold="true" box="[189,310,1879,1905]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="6" pageNumber="74" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B924EA810379EF671E897824FEF76A30" bold="true" box="[189,310,1879,1905]" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36930379EF671E8978F4FAB76AA8" blockId="6.[189,1399,1927,2025]" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">
The new species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D100379EF671C6178FBFB836AE0" authority="(O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1874)" baseAuthorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[597,1090,1927,1953]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venatrix">
<emphasis id="B924EA810379EF671C6178FBFD146AE0" box="[597,725,1928,1953]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">B. venatrix</emphasis>
(O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1874)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D100379EF671A4E78FBFDCE6A84" authority="Marusik, Fomichev &amp; Omelko, 2014" authorityName="Marusik, Fomichev &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2014" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koponeni">
<emphasis id="B924EA810379EF671A4E78FBFB4D6AE0" box="[1146,1164,1928,1953]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B924EA810379EF671AAF78F4FAC66AE0" box="[1179,1287,1927,1953]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">koponeni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B620379EF671B3978F4FDCE6A84" author="Marusik Y. M. &amp; Fomichev A. A. &amp; Omelko M. M." pageId="6" pageNumber="74" pagination="187 - 213" refId="ref17777" refString="Marusik Y. M., Fomichev A. A. &amp; Omelko M. M. 2014. A survey of East Palaearctic Gnaphosidae (Araneae). 1. On the Berlandina Dalmas, 1922 (Gnaphosinae) from Mongolia and adjacent regions. Zootaxa 3827 (2): 187 - 213. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3827.2.4" type="journal article" year="2014">Marusik, Fomichev &amp; Omelko, 2014</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by having a broad embolar base (
<emphasis id="B924EA810379EF671D8C78D9FC186A85" box="[952,985,1962,1988]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">Eb</emphasis>
) with a similar sclerotized apical outgrowth (
<emphasis id="B924EA810379EF671F7C78BCFEA86AA8" box="[328,361,1999,2025]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">Ao</emphasis>
) parallel to a bent, long embolus and a basal process (
<emphasis id="B924EA810379EF671DC378BCFBD96AA9" box="[1015,1048,1999,2024]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="74">Po</emphasis>
). In the new species, the two
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BEF36930378EF661E897E7AFE8A6C95" blockId="7.[189,1399,265,468]" pageId="7" pageNumber="75">
elements of the embolar base are pointed (vs shallowly divided with the process small and curved in 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D100378EF661E8B7E5EFE866C07" authorityName="Marusik, Fomichev &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2014" box="[191,327,300,327]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koponeni">
<emphasis id="B924EA810378EF661E8B7E5EFF0E6C07" box="[191,207,301,326]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="75">B</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B924EA810378EF661EE87E5FFE866C07" box="[220,327,300,326]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="75">koponeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B620378EF661FB57E5FFDA76C07" author="Marusik Y. M. &amp; Fomichev A. A. &amp; Omelko M. M." box="[385,614,300,326]" pageId="7" pageNumber="75" pagination="187 - 213" refId="ref17777" refString="Marusik Y. M., Fomichev A. A. &amp; Omelko M. M. 2014. A survey of East Palaearctic Gnaphosidae (Araneae). 1. On the Berlandina Dalmas, 1922 (Gnaphosinae) from Mongolia and adjacent regions. Zootaxa 3827 (2): 187 - 213. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3827.2.4" type="journal article" year="2014">
Marusik 
<emphasis id="B924EA810378EF661FD37E5EFDE16C07" box="[487,544,300,326]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="75">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
: figs 32, 34, and the basal process bearing a very pointed sclerotized tooth in 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D100378EF661F117E23FE696C28" baseAuthorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[293,424,336,361]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venatrix">
<emphasis id="B924EA810378EF661F117E23FE696C28" box="[293,424,336,361]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="75">B. venatrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B620378EF661FDD7E23FDAE6C2B" author="Levy G." box="[489,623,335,362]" pageId="7" pageNumber="75" pagination="919 - 981" refId="ref17523" refString="Levy G. 1995. Revision of the spider subfamily Gnaphosinae in Israel (Araneae: Gnaphosidae). Journal of Natural History 29 (4): 919 - 981. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222939500770351" type="journal article" year="1995">Levy 1995</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 57, not present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D100378EF661DBD7E23FBE86C28" authority="Zamani &amp; Chatzaki &amp; Esyunin &amp; Marusik, 2021" authorityName="Zamani &amp; Chatzaki &amp; Esyunin &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2021" box="[905,1065,336,361]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="artaxerxes" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B924EA810378EF661DBD7E23FBE86C28" box="[905,1065,336,361]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="75">B. artaxerxes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21757FA0378EF661A067E23FB556C2B" box="[1074,1172,336,362]" pageId="7" pageNumber="75" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
). Also, the median apophysis in 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D100378EF661F6F7E00FE386CCD" authority="Zamani &amp; Chatzaki &amp; Esyunin &amp; Marusik, 2021" authorityName="Zamani &amp; Chatzaki &amp; Esyunin &amp; Marusik" authorityYear="2021" box="[347,505,371,396]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="artaxerxes" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B924EA810378EF661F6F7E00FE386CCD" box="[347,505,371,396]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="75">B. artaxerxes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21757FA0378EF661C347E00FD9D6CCC" box="[512,604,371,397]" pageId="7" pageNumber="75" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is bent prolaterally and located under the apical outgrowth’s curve (vs straight and longer, reaching the height of the embolus in 
<taxonomicName id="4C504D100378EF661D9B7EE4FBFF6CF1" authorityName="Marusik, Fomichev &amp; Omelko" authorityYear="2014" box="[943,1086,406,432]" class="Arachnida" family="Gnaphosidae" genus="Berlandina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="7" pageNumber="75" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="koponeni">
<emphasis id="B924EA810378EF661D9B7EE4FBFF6CF1" box="[943,1086,406,432]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="75">B. koponeni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFC14B620378EF661A4B7EE5FAB36CF1" author="Marusik Y. M. &amp; Fomichev A. A. &amp; Omelko M. M." box="[1151,1394,406,432]" pageId="7" pageNumber="75" pagination="187 - 213" refId="ref17777" refString="Marusik Y. M., Fomichev A. A. &amp; Omelko M. M. 2014. A survey of East Palaearctic Gnaphosidae (Araneae). 1. On the Berlandina Dalmas, 1922 (Gnaphosinae) from Mongolia and adjacent regions. Zootaxa 3827 (2): 187 - 213. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3827.2.4" type="journal article" year="2014">
Marusik 
<emphasis id="B924EA810378EF661AD87EE4FAE86CF1" box="[1260,1321,406,432]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="75">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
: figs 34–35).
</paragraph>
